//
// LLAMA-3.2-1B int4-AWQ compile-only smoke test: builds the int4 + bf16
// prefill stitcher ELFs + flash_attn through the AIR -> AIE -> aiecc ->
// Peano pipeline. No NPU dispatch.
//
// The default AWQ checkpoint (amd/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-awq-uint4-asym-g128-
// bf16-lmhead) is NOT gated, so HF_TOKEN is not required for compile —
// unlike run_npu2_verify.lit which fetches the gated upstream tokenizer.
//
// Gated on ryzen_ai_npu2 because matmul_int4_packed and the bf16 stitchers
// hardcode the AIE2P target (arch="aie2p"); running this on a non-NPU2
// context would compile artifacts that cannot be exercised on the host
// runner. The actual compile does not touch the NPU device.
//
// REQUIRES: ryzen_ai_npu2, peano
//
// RUN: mkdir -p test_peano_compile
// RUN: cd test_peano_compile
// RUN: make -f %S/Makefile clean
// RUN: make -f %S/Makefile compile PEANO_INSTALL_DIR=%PEANO_INSTALL_DIR | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: Compilation passed.
